278
00:25:10,807 --> 00:25:14,887
Mr. Noh Manners. You're done for.

279
00:25:19,517 --> 00:25:22,107
Come on in

280
00:25:25,567 --> 00:25:26,567
Sir.

281
00:25:27,367 --> 00:25:29,327
The study guides meeting ran over.

282
00:25:29,407 --> 00:25:30,407
I'm sorry.

283
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:32,537
What? You little…

284
00:25:33,707 --> 00:25:34,707
Oh, I see.

285
00:25:37,457 --> 00:25:42,207
Things can get delayed sometimes.
It happens, you know?

286
00:25:42,297 --> 00:25:44,377
It's okay.

287
00:25:46,007 --> 00:25:47,547
You may get back to work.

288
00:25:47,637 --> 00:25:48,717
Yes, sir.

289
00:25:51,177 --> 00:25:53,267
Hey, have you seen him?

290
00:25:53,847 --> 00:25:54,677
Who…

291
00:25:55,267 --> 00:25:57,897
That man who works for Ms. Baek.

292
00:25:57,977 --> 00:25:59,477
Oh, you mean, Mr. Cho?

293
00:25:59,977 --> 00:26:02,777
Yes, him. You've never seen him
somewhere else besides Baek Edu?

294
00:26:02,857 --> 00:26:04,437
No, I haven't.

295
00:26:04,527 --> 00:26:08,197
Really? Why do I get this feeling
that I've seen him somewhere before?

296
00:26:14,447 --> 00:26:16,537
I wonder how Sooho is doing.

297
00:26:17,117 --> 00:26:18,747
-Should I go say hi?
-No, you can't.

298
00:26:19,877 --> 00:26:21,337
-Why not?
-It's late.

299
00:26:21,417 --> 00:26:24,087
No, it's not. Besides, I'm just saying hi.

300
00:26:24,667 --> 00:26:25,717
No, you can't.

301
00:26:25,877 --> 00:26:28,887
I have a lot to do.
Please go now. Drive home safely.

302
00:26:28,967 --> 00:26:30,387
But…

303
00:26:38,727 --> 00:26:41,267
Do-re-mi-fa-sol

304
00:26:42,477 --> 00:26:43,647
Why can't I keep it up high?

305
00:26:45,987 --> 00:26:49,857
Okay, shall we solve the next question?

306
00:26:51,277 --> 00:26:53,577
Okay, shall we solve the next question?

307
00:26:54,287 --> 00:26:56,827
Escaping from the Enlightenment ideas,

308
00:26:58,707 --> 00:27:01,287
seeking new ways of employing prosody,

309
00:27:01,787 --> 00:27:06,587
and experimental mind…

310
00:27:08,127 --> 00:27:09,127
Sorry.

311
00:27:25,567 --> 00:27:28,987
MY DEAR MR. NOH

312
00:27:35,907 --> 00:27:38,037
MY DEAR MS. LEE

313
00:27:38,117 --> 00:27:40,747
Why doesn't she answer my calls
whenever she goes home these days?

314
00:27:52,337 --> 00:27:53,717
I found a good restaurant.

315
00:27:54,297 --> 00:27:56,967
It's a bit far,
but I heard that it's really good.

316
00:27:57,517 --> 00:27:58,387
Let's go there.

317
00:27:59,017 --> 00:28:01,637
I'm sorry, but I have so much to do today.

318
00:28:01,727 --> 00:28:03,267
Let's just eat around here today.

319
00:28:04,767 --> 00:28:05,977
But I heard it's really good.

320
00:28:06,477 --> 00:28:08,937
SUSHI SANGMU, RAW SALMON, TUNA
SUSHI WITH DELICIOUS RICE

321
00:28:16,737 --> 00:28:17,577
It's delicious.

322
00:28:18,907 --> 00:28:19,997
Isn't this place good?

323
00:28:20,287 --> 00:28:21,497
Yes.

324
00:28:22,077 --> 00:28:23,077
By the way,

325
00:28:24,167 --> 00:28:25,837
what do you need to do?

326
00:28:29,587 --> 00:28:30,417
Come on. Eat up now.

327
00:28:42,847 --> 00:28:44,097
The key point is…

328
00:28:53,567 --> 00:28:55,027
The key point here is…

