00:28:56,197 --> 00:28:58,577
CLASSICS

330
00:28:58,657 --> 00:29:00,537
Okay, contemporary literature is…

331
00:29:22,137 --> 00:29:23,267
Ms. Lee.

332
00:29:23,347 --> 00:29:25,397
You're neglecting your duties lately.

333
00:29:26,267 --> 00:29:27,227
I'm sorry.

334
00:29:28,567 --> 00:29:29,567
Do you think

335
00:29:30,977 --> 00:29:32,737
you've got me wrapped around your finger?

336
00:29:33,647 --> 00:29:34,487
Sorry?

337
00:29:35,237 --> 00:29:39,327
Don't you think you're neglecting
your duties to your boyfriend lately?

338
00:29:39,407 --> 00:29:41,787
I've been getting stood up
every day these days.

339
00:29:41,867 --> 00:29:43,787
Have you been
going on dates with some other guy?

340
00:29:43,867 --> 00:29:46,707
Since you've got me
wrapped around your finger,

341
00:29:46,787 --> 00:29:48,587
you don't feel the need
to be nice anymore?

342
00:29:50,747 --> 00:29:52,757
That's nonsense.

343
00:29:53,417 --> 00:29:55,877
Then, can we go on a date this weekend?

344
00:29:55,967 --> 00:29:57,927
Let's do that next weekend instead.

345
00:30:12,817 --> 00:30:15,527
What kind of a couple
doesn't go on a date on a weekend?

346
00:30:15,607 --> 00:30:16,987
That's not a couple then.

347
00:30:27,247 --> 00:30:28,327
What?

348
00:30:33,877 --> 00:30:34,707
Gojin.

349
00:30:35,797 --> 00:30:38,217
Oh, Sooho!

350
00:30:38,297 --> 00:30:41,007
I've been counting down until the weekend
to come over to your place.

351
00:30:42,507 --> 00:30:43,347
May I come in?

352
00:30:44,927 --> 00:30:46,807
Sure… Come on in.

353
00:30:46,887 --> 00:30:47,767
All right!

354
00:30:54,357 --> 00:30:56,817
Wow. It's amazing.

355
00:30:59,857 --> 00:31:01,197
I've never seen a place like this.

356
00:31:10,327 --> 00:31:12,877
Wow, your sofa is so nice.

357
00:31:21,177 --> 00:31:24,007
Hello? Sorry? What did you say?

358
00:31:26,097 --> 00:31:27,637
It's practically a department store.

359
00:31:35,107 --> 00:31:36,107
Do you like them?

360
00:31:37,437 --> 00:31:39,107
Do you want to keep them?

361
00:31:40,027 --> 00:31:41,737
-Seriously?
-Yes.

362
00:31:42,407 --> 00:31:44,367
You can take anything else you like.

363
00:31:44,947 --> 00:31:46,077
Gojin!

364
00:31:46,157 --> 00:31:47,447
I love you!

365
00:31:50,917 --> 00:31:53,627
Okay, Sooho. I'm glad you're happy,

366
00:31:53,957 --> 00:31:55,457
but can you get off of me, please?

367
00:31:55,707 --> 00:31:57,627
I'm already taken, you know?

368
00:32:00,677 --> 00:32:02,297
I don't want anyone
taking away my big sis.

369
00:32:04,297 --> 00:32:05,887
She's like a mom to me.

370
00:32:07,517 --> 00:32:10,767
But since it's you, I think I can
make an exception to trust you with her.

371
00:32:15,817 --> 00:32:18,397
CHARACTERISTICS OF THE KOREAN LANGUAGE
IN THE MIDDLE AGES

372
00:32:24,117 --> 00:32:28,237
Okay, today, we'll talk about
the characteristics of… Middle Korean…

373
00:32:28,747 --> 00:32:31,457
The characteristics of the Korean language
in the middle ages…

374
00:32:35,957 --> 00:32:36,997
Today…

375
00:32:53,057 --> 00:32:54,057
Today…

376
00:33:03,147 --> 00:33:04,777
To be honest, I felt shy at the beginning,

377
00:33:04,857 --> 00:33:06,947
so I hid my face like this to practice.

378
00:33:09,827 --> 00:33:11,247
I love you.

379
00:33:11,997 --> 00:33:12,907
Hey, Okhee.

380
00:33:12,997 --> 00:33:14,117
Gosh, you startled me.

381
00:33:14,207 --> 00:33:16,207
You have a lot of masks, right?
Can I borrow them?

382
00:33:16,287 --> 00:33:18,127
-What for?
-I need them for something.

383
00:33:18,877 --> 00:33:20,627
They're all over there. Take them.

384
00:33:23,047 --> 00:33:25,887
By the way, have you seen Sooho?
I haven't seen him since earlier.

385
00:33:25,967 --> 00:33:27,467
Maybe he went to a convenience store.

386
00:33:31,887 --> 00:33:33,307
Sooho, where are you?

387
00:33:34,687 --> 00:33:36,647
Where? Mr. Noh Manners'--

388
00:33:38,107 --> 00:33:40,437
I mean, Mr. Noh's place?

389
00:33:45,237 --> 00:33:46,447
Sooho, you have a death wish?

390
00:33:47,567 --> 00:33:49,237
What are you doing here?

391
00:33:49,327 --> 00:33:50,987
I asked him to come hang out.

392
00:33:51,077 --> 00:33:52,247
Please don't take his side.

393
00:33:52,747 --> 00:33:53,747
Wait!

394
00:33:58,707 --> 00:34:00,287
You can kill me later,

395
00:34:01,667 --> 00:34:02,837
but let me eat first.

396
00:34:05,547 --> 00:34:06,717
I'm hungry.

397
00:34:19,107 --> 00:34:20,107
It's so good.

398
00:34:21,567 --> 00:34:24,897
Wow, I can't believe I get to eat
jjajangmyeon in such a fancy house.

399
00:34:25,567 --> 00:34:27,357
I'd have no regrets even if I died now.

400
00:34:27,447 --> 00:34:28,947
-Hey, you--
-Hey.

401
00:34:29,447 --> 00:34:31,407
Let him eat in peace.

402
00:34:32,237 --> 00:34:35,157
Here you go, honey. Open up.

403
00:34:35,657 --> 00:34:36,827
My goodness. Eat up.

404
00:34:36,907 --> 00:34:39,537
She's right.
It's nice to all eat together.

405
00:34:39,627 --> 00:34:43,087
Please stop taking his side.
He'll act up thinking you've got his back.

406
00:34:43,747 --> 00:34:45,207
I'm his little bro starting today.

407
00:34:48,677 --> 00:34:50,757
Oh, you didn't forget
about tomorrow's dinner, right?

408
00:34:51,387 --> 00:34:54,097
Of course not. I've been dying waiting.

409
00:34:54,557 --> 00:34:55,427
Dinner?

410
00:34:56,137 --> 00:34:57,227
What dinner?

411
00:34:57,307 --> 00:35:00,687
Oh, our high school friends
will be visiting Seoul tomorrow.

412
00:35:01,267 --> 00:35:02,227
Oh, I see.

413
00:35:02,727 --> 00:35:04,227
I heard Heeseok is coming too.

414
00:35:04,817 --> 00:35:06,487
-Heeseok?
-Yes.

415
00:35:06,567 --> 00:35:08,817
You cried your eyes out
when Heeseok went to the military.

416
00:35:08,907 --> 00:35:10,817
Yes, I cried so much.

417
00:35:11,817 --> 00:35:12,777
-When?
-The military?

418
00:35:12,867 --> 00:35:13,867
-What time?
-7 p.m.

419
00:35:13,947 --> 00:35:15,657
-She cried?
-Did you make a reservation?

420
00:35:15,747 --> 00:35:17,907
-Is he that first love?
-I did. This place.

421
00:35:18,657 --> 00:35:19,667
Isn't it totally nice?

422
00:35:19,747 --> 00:35:22,587
Yes, it is. The food looks so good.

423
00:35:23,207 --> 00:35:26,087
It's so great to see you guys.

424
00:35:26,167 --> 00:35:27,337
A tiring trip to Seoul, right?

425
00:35:27,417 --> 00:35:30,337
Not at all. Thanks to you guys,
we get to visit Seoul.

426
00:35:30,927 --> 00:35:33,347
I got to get away from Gangneung
to get some fresh air

427
00:35:33,427 --> 00:35:35,637
and get a break
from my childcare duties. It's so great.

428
00:35:35,717 --> 00:35:38,267
Hey, let's all go
to my theater company tomorrow.

429
00:35:38,347 --> 00:35:41,727
Of course.
We've got to see you act, Okhee.

430
00:35:44,067 --> 00:35:44,897
Are you dating?

431
00:35:45,567 --> 00:35:47,737
Your face is glowing.

432
00:35:47,817 --> 00:35:49,357
-She is--
-No, I'm not!

433
00:35:50,397 --> 00:35:51,527
Well…

434
00:35:51,607 --> 00:35:55,237
Anyway, it's so great to see you guys.

435
00:35:55,327 --> 00:35:58,037
It's good to see you guys,
but I'm hungry now.

436
00:35:58,117 --> 00:36:00,247
Let's eat first. Pick now.

437
00:36:00,327 --> 00:36:01,367
What should we eat?

438
00:36:22,017 --> 00:36:23,147
Hello.

439
00:36:23,227 --> 00:36:26,227
I'm Noh Gojin, Ms. Sina's boyfriend.

440
00:36:27,727 --> 00:36:29,647
-What?
-Oh my.

441
00:36:29,737 --> 00:36:31,777
-My goodness.
-Her boyfriend?

442
00:36:32,657 --> 00:36:34,027
-Oh my.
-Gosh.

443
00:36:34,117 --> 00:36:35,617
What are you doing here?

444
00:36:35,697 --> 00:36:39,577
Your friends are in town.
Of course, I should come say hello.

445
00:36:40,537 --> 00:36:42,957
-Oh my.
-Unbelievable.

446
00:36:43,827 --> 00:36:45,667
Please eat anything you'd like.

447
00:36:45,747 --> 00:36:49,007
And I reserved a suite at a hotel.

448
00:36:50,667 --> 00:36:52,467
-A suite?
-Amazing!

449
00:36:53,047 --> 00:36:54,337
You haven't seen each other much.

450
00:36:54,837 --> 00:36:56,597
You've got to have fun all night.

451
00:36:58,427 --> 00:37:00,977
Lee Sina, you're so lucky.

452
00:37:01,137 --> 00:37:03,347
Where did you find yourself
such a great boyfriend?

453
00:37:03,437 --> 00:37:05,437
You make Gangwon Province proud.

454
00:37:09,817 --> 00:37:10,897
Are you looking for someone?

455
00:37:11,777 --> 00:37:14,237
Sorry? Well…

456
00:37:15,487 --> 00:37:17,867
I guess Mr. Heeseok isn't here yet?

457
00:37:19,657 --> 00:37:20,827
Are you referring to me?

458
00:37:25,617 --> 00:37:26,577
That's Heeseok.

459
00:37:27,747 --> 00:37:30,127
When she entered
the military out of the blue,

460
00:37:30,207 --> 00:37:32,297
we all cried our eyes out together.

461
00:37:34,337 --> 00:37:35,177
Salute!

462
00:37:36,087 --> 00:37:38,927
Sergeant First Class Oh Heeseok.
Nice to meet you.

463
00:37:41,347 --> 00:37:42,347
Oh, I see.

464
00:37:43,427 --> 00:37:44,387
You're Ms. Heeseok.

465
00:37:46,147 --> 00:37:47,357
Nice to meet you.

466
00:37:55,527 --> 00:37:56,907
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

467
00:37:57,277 --> 00:37:59,447
-I'm drinking too much.
-My goodness.

468
00:38:00,867 --> 00:38:02,327
Thank you so much.

469
00:38:03,447 --> 00:38:04,707
Have fun.

470
00:38:06,287 --> 00:38:07,997
But you still have to
think about me, okay?

471
00:38:09,707 --> 00:38:10,537
I'll call you.

472
00:38:12,377 --> 00:38:14,087
Gosh, I drank so much.

473
00:38:16,297 --> 00:38:19,757
-My goodness.
-You said you weren't dating.

474
00:38:26,887 --> 00:38:28,307
-And?
-Do you remember?

475
00:38:28,397 --> 00:38:30,607
Your boyfriend at the time--

476
00:38:34,567 --> 00:38:35,607
Are you all right?

477
00:38:36,237 --> 00:38:37,407
Yes, I am.

478
00:38:38,277 --> 00:38:39,617
My goodness.

479
00:38:40,197 --> 00:38:43,157
My car was pulling in. You just jumped
in front of it without even looking.

480
00:38:43,487 --> 00:38:44,367
Watch it!

481
00:38:46,117 --> 00:38:47,117
What did you say?

482
00:38:48,667 --> 00:38:49,997
You almost hit a person,

483
00:38:50,077 --> 00:38:51,787
but you didn't even apologize. How rude!

484
00:38:53,377 --> 00:38:56,007
A person should watch out for cars. Okay?

485
00:38:57,337 --> 00:38:59,137
You watch out.

486
00:38:59,797 --> 00:39:00,797
Oh my.

487
00:39:02,297 --> 00:39:03,677
How dare you talk so rudely.

488
00:39:03,757 --> 00:39:05,637
You were rude first.

489
00:39:05,717 --> 00:39:09,057
What? How ridiculous.

490
00:39:12,147 --> 00:39:12,977
Sis.

491
00:39:14,977 --> 00:39:16,147
What's going on?

492
00:39:16,357 --> 00:39:17,487
Sooyeong.

493
00:39:17,567 --> 00:39:20,447
Well, they're the ones who were careless
and almost ran into my car,

494
00:39:20,527 --> 00:39:22,947
but they got upset
and started to argue with me.

495
00:39:25,157 --> 00:39:25,997
Let's just go.

496
00:39:26,077 --> 00:39:29,247
No. I heard that there are
many insurance frauds these days.

497
00:39:29,827 --> 00:39:31,077
Maybe that's what you are.

498
00:39:31,667 --> 00:39:32,497
What did you say?

499
00:39:32,587 --> 00:39:33,667
How dare you call us that!

500
00:39:33,747 --> 00:39:35,747
What? I know I am right.

501
00:39:36,337 --> 00:39:37,377
How old are you?

502
00:39:37,467 --> 00:39:39,587
-How dare you talk down to me?
-Gosh!

503
00:39:39,677 --> 00:39:40,757
-Sis!
-Don't talk down to me.

504
00:39:40,837 --> 00:39:42,337
-Sis!
-Let go of me!

505
00:39:42,967 --> 00:39:43,847
-Oh my!
-Sina!

506
00:39:43,927 --> 00:39:44,927
Oh no.

507
00:39:45,257 --> 00:39:46,427
-Ms. Sina!
-Are you okay?

508
00:39:47,177 --> 00:39:48,427
Don't touch her!

509
00:40:04,407 --> 00:40:05,447
Let's go.

510
00:40:23,927 --> 00:40:25,887
Why are you still here?

511
00:40:27,347 --> 00:40:29,727
I wanted to see
Lee Sina's face one more time.

512
00:40:32,387 --> 00:40:35,187
I didn't fall down
because of Ms. Sooyeong.

513
00:40:37,727 --> 00:40:38,567
Go now.

514
00:40:39,687 --> 00:40:44,237
Forget about everything
and have fun with your friends, okay?

515
00:41:24,527 --> 00:41:27,697
I told you not to get her involved.
She has nothing to do with our problem.

516
00:41:28,657 --> 00:41:30,077
Are you really Noh Gojin?

517
00:41:31,617 --> 00:41:33,787
Are you the same Noh Gojin
who I used to know?

518
00:41:37,537 --> 00:41:39,587
What did I do so wrong?

519
00:41:41,457 --> 00:41:43,507
I've only loved you.

520
00:41:48,847 --> 00:41:51,307
You come and go as you please.

521
00:41:52,557 --> 00:41:53,847
That's what love is to you?

522
00:41:57,607 --> 00:41:59,647
I can explain everything.

523
00:42:00,067 --> 00:42:01,357
It was beyond my control.

524
00:42:01,937 --> 00:42:03,317
Do I really have to hear about it?

525
00:42:05,317 --> 00:42:06,407
After all this time?

526
00:42:13,407 --> 00:42:16,117
If you leave now, I'll never forgive you.

527
00:42:24,337 --> 00:42:26,587
What did I do so wrong?

528
00:42:29,677 --> 00:42:30,757
What did I do?

529
00:42:32,887 --> 00:42:37,307
GOTOP EDUCATION

530
00:42:44,107 --> 00:42:46,237
-This is--
-It's a second ledger set.

531
00:42:46,697 --> 00:42:49,237
Mr. Noh has been evading taxes.

532
00:42:49,317 --> 00:42:50,447
Mr. Noh--

533
00:42:52,617 --> 00:42:55,697
Mr. Noh has been evading taxes?

534
00:42:56,907 --> 00:42:57,787
Yes.

535
00:42:59,327 --> 00:43:03,497
You just need to be honest
